\boxed{\text{The American Legion}}

W. C. Handy wrote *"The St. Louis Blues"* (1914) for the **St. Louis Blues** baseball team, but the question refers to the **American Legion**, which was involved in the 1946 **Battle of Athens** (a racial conflict in Georgia). The song connection is tangential here; the key link is the Legion’s role in the battle.
